snippet.textDisplay: During the 1918 Spanish Flu, the media downplayed the dangers, causing many to not take it seriously. The Spanish Flu of 1918 killed more Americans than World War 1, World War 2, Vietnam, Korea, Iraq, and Afghanistan combined. Whether you’re young or not, we all need to take preventative measures to avoid spreading it. If you’re not old, someday you will be. Pay attention every couple of years a new virus spreads, meaning one will spread at some point in your life when up in the age bracket. I am young, fit, healthy, have no chronic illness at all, but somehow got pneumonia years back. Reasons were probably I didn’t take getting sick serious. I hardly ever get sick. I see a bunch of young adults with all kinds of allergies and weak immune systems, not to mention over-weight. Here in Texas I’m seeing more people are coughing badly and there’s no test kit for them. We all have older parents/grandparents. This can also disrupt the economy. Pay attention to how fast it’s spreading.
